<subSubSection pageId="133" pageNumber="134" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="133.[151,1437,1563,2023]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1707,1734]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A large heavy bodied species (12.0 mm long) with orange pronotum and black elytra which may be narrowly orange marked across their bases; distinguished from the similarly coloured 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1110,1233,1744,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1110,1233,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">P. calceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1239,1369,1744,1771]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1239,1362,1744,1770]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by its size (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[211,306,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceata">
<emphasis box="[211,306,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">calceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<quantity box="[339,404,1780,1807]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
long) and the outline of the MPP (in 
<taxonomicName box="[824,927,1781,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitescens">
<emphasis box="[824,927,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">nitescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is short and apically acute; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1293,1388,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceata">
<emphasis box="[1293,1388,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">calceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is about as long as wide and apically truncated).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="136" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="133" pageNumber="134" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="133.[151,1437,1563,2023]" lastBlockId="136.[151,1437,153,1619]" lastPageId="136" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,1851,1878]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Redescription of male</emphasis>
. 12.0 mm long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[743,906,1852,1878]" captionStart="FIGURES 422−429" captionStartId="134.[151,264,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[213,1349,183,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@134.[213,1375,183,1892]" captionTargetPageId="134" captionText="FIGURES 422−429. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. male. 422, 423 Borneo coll. Chaper (MNHN); 424−429 Sarawak coll Polunin (ANIC). 422, 424 habitus dorsal; 423 habitus ventral; 425, 426 terminal abdomen: 425 ventral; 426 dorsal; 427−429 aedeagal sheath: 427 dorsal; 428 ventral (outline of lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite arrowed); 429 left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508262/files/figure.png" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">Figs 422−424</figureCitation>
): pronotum, MS and MN orange; elytra almost black, having humerus and narrow basal area orange in 
<typeStatus box="[762,814,1889,1915]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
; head between eyes, antennae and palpi very dark brown almost black; venter of pro and mesothorax yellowish, of metathorax slightly darker (venter of all thoracic segments light brown in 
<typeStatus box="[316,369,1961,1987]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
); legs yellowish (light brown in 
<typeStatus box="[729,779,1961,1987]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">type</typeStatus>
) with all tibiae and tarsi dark brown; basal abdominal ventrites yellowish; 
<date box="[337,373,1996,2022]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">V6</date>
, 7 with whitish LO, 
<date box="[601,635,1997,2023]" pageId="133" pageNumber="134">V7</date>
LO retracted from all margins in Leluan male, retracted along posterior margin only in 
<typeStatus box="[320,372,153,179]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
; all abdominal tergites yellowish in Leluan male (colour not observed in 
<typeStatus box="[1178,1231,153,179]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
). Pronotum: width subequal to (in 
<typeStatus box="[321,373,189,215]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
), or slightly wider than humeral width; lateral margins strongly divergent and posterolateral corners rounded and projecting. Elytron: slightly convex sided; interstitial lines not well defined. Head: GHW 
<date box="[1338,1372,225,251]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">6 x</date>
SIW: antennal sockets very close but not contiguous. Mouthparts: apical labial palpomere laterally flattened of the form of a broad triangle with inner edge dentate (3 teeth). Antennae:&gt; GHW but not exceeding 
<date box="[1116,1150,297,323]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">2 x</date>
GHW; all segments elongate (longer than 
<date box="[348,383,333,359]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">2 x</date>
width) slender. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[687,847,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 422−429" captionStartId="134.[151,264,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[213,1349,183,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@134.[213,1375,183,1892]" captionTargetPageId="134" captionText="FIGURES 422−429. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. male. 422, 423 Borneo coll. Chaper (MNHN); 424−429 Sarawak coll Polunin (ANIC). 422, 424 habitus dorsal; 423 habitus ventral; 425, 426 terminal abdomen: 425 ventral; 426 dorsal; 427−429 aedeagal sheath: 427 dorsal; 428 ventral (outline of lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite arrowed); 429 left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508262/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 423, 425</figureCitation>
): posterior margin of 
<date box="[1088,1122,333,359]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V7</date>
without PLP and with short broadly rounded MPP; T8 with truncate posterior margin and subparallel sided, anterolateral prolongations long slender expanded vertically. Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[684,849,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 422−429" captionStartId="134.[151,264,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[213,1349,183,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@134.[213,1375,183,1892]" captionTargetPageId="134" captionText="FIGURES 422−429. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. male. 422, 423 Borneo coll. Chaper (MNHN); 424−429 Sarawak coll Polunin (ANIC). 422, 424 habitus dorsal; 423 habitus ventral; 425, 426 terminal abdomen: 425 ventral; 426 dorsal; 427−429 aedeagal sheath: 427 dorsal; 428 ventral (outline of lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite arrowed); 429 left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508262/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 427−429</figureCitation>
): tergite with anterior transverse darkened separate plate associated with but not clearly attached to the anterior margin of the sheath tergite; basal ¾ of sheath sternite with sclerotized margins very narrow, expanding in apical ¼ where it is terminated by broad paired rounded hairy lobes which are united across their bases by a darkened semicircular piece; dark transverse strip of cuticle (outline of lobes arrowed in 
<figureCitation box="[375,472,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 422−429" captionStartId="134.[151,264,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[213,1349,183,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@134.[213,1375,183,1892]" captionTargetPageId="134" captionText="FIGURES 422−429. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. male. 422, 423 Borneo coll. Chaper (MNHN); 424−429 Sarawak coll Polunin (ANIC). 422, 424 habitus dorsal; 423 habitus ventral; 425, 426 terminal abdomen: 425 ventral; 426 dorsal; 427−429 aedeagal sheath: 427 dorsal; 428 ventral (outline of lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite arrowed); 429 left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508262" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508262/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Fig. 428</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[615,778,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 430−432</figureCitation>
): slightly more than twice as long as wide and evenly wide along its entire length; BP in two well cuticularised narrow parts; membranous apical section of LL with dense line of long hairs inside their lateral margins, and quite widely expanded in horizontal plane; ML tapering to a rounded narrow apex, not much shorter than LL; darker basal portion of LL with apical 1/3 separated, rest of LL fused at their bases; anterior margin of basal portion of LL asymmetrical, produced and rounded on its left.
</paragraph>
