<paragraph blockId="136.[151,1437,153,1619]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,729,755]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Female</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[302,462,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 433−436</figureCitation>
. Assigned on the basis of its size, locality and distinctive colour. 
<quantity box="[1205,1285,729,755]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[159,320,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 433, 434</figureCitation>
): pronotum dingy yellowish with faint traces of very small median brown markings; underlying fat body is retracted and confuses interpretation of colour; MS, MN dingy yellow; elytra black shiny; head, antennae and palpi black; venter of thorax and abdominal ventrites anterior to LO brown; legs brown except for dark brown tibiae and tarsi; ventrites 2–5 semitransparent and underlying fat body is visible beneath cuticle; LO in 
<date box="[1312,1346,873,899]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V6</date>
creamy white retracted from anterior margin of 
<date box="[592,630,909,935]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V6</date>
; 
<date box="[640,676,909,935]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V7</date>
, 8 semitransparent orange yellow; all abdominal tergites orange yellow, semitransparent. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[518,617,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Fig. 433</figureCitation>
): median anterior margin not produced anteriorly; lateral margins strongly divergent; posterolateral corners rounded and produced beyond midposterior margin; width greater than humeral width. Elytron: slightly convex sided; interstitial line 3 irregularly defined. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1277,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Figs 433, 434</figureCitation>
): 
<date box="[1296,1329,1017,1043]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V7</date>
posterior margin broadly emarginated with posterolateral corners rounded; 
<date box="[888,921,1053,1079]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V8</date>
posterior margin emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1372,1052,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Fig. 435</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin well coloured and separated from rest of ventrite by a clear membranous position. Genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Fig. 437</figureCitation>
): styli with both segments elongated slender, basal segment slightly longer than apical. Reproductive system (
<figureCitation box="[160,259,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 430–436" captionStartId="135.[151,264,1893,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1364,166,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@135.[218,1369,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="135" captionText="FIGURES 430–436. Pygoluciola nitescens comb. nov. 430−432 male (Sarawak coll. Polunin;ANIC); 433−436 female (Ranau; NHML). 430−432 aedeagus: 430 ventral; 431 dorsal; 432 left lateral; 433 habitus dorsal; 434 habitus ventral; 435 abdominal ventrite 8, ventral; 436 reproductive system, ovipositor to right, spermatophore digesting gland and spermatheca to left (arrow indicates area of bursa and possible thin bursa plates). Scale lines are 1 mm in 430, 435 and 2 mm in 433." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508264/files/figure.png" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Fig. 436</figureCitation>
): bursa, SDG and spermatheca observed through abdomen soaked for an hour in cold KOH; bursa plates may be present but not clearly observed (white arrow indicates bursa).
</paragraph>
